SENSOR RESET CORRECTION - Sensor movement likely occurred during one of the low stage ice flows. HWM was unobtainable on field visit (non-discernible). Therefore drift correction applied.

The slow recession was calculated by the averaging of historical recession constants between winter measurements (See '10BE001_HISTORICAL_RECESSION' sheet). Placement of the recession line (recession constant k = 0.0056; standard deviation = 0.0014) sought to minimize the percent difference from the winter measurements acquired. Override: Log Linear‌Q(t) = 458e^(-0.0042t)‌
